                                                                  8237 1451
 The resolved resonance evaluation utilized transmission and      8237 1451
 capture data sets [ref01-06] in the SAMMY code [ref07].          8237 1451
                                                                  8237 1451
 Base resonance parameters taken from ENDF/B-VIII [ref08].        8237 1451
 The effective scattering radius R' was changed to 9.75 fm to     8237 1451
 get proper potential scattering term [ref09].                    8237 1451
                                                                  8237 1451
 Constraining the capture cross section was done with Maxwellian  8237 1451
 Averaged Cross Sections (MACS) at 30 keV. Work by Beer, Allen    8237 1451
 [ref10], Weissman [ref11] demonstrated that MACS(30 keV) should  8237 1451
 be 0.35 mb. Due to the poor capture data on this isotope, many   8237 1451
 resonance have an average radiation width which was changed to   8237 1451
 get the above MACS(30 keV). In addition, a direct capture        8237 1451
 component was added in MF-3. Capture cross section around 10 eV  8237 1451
 is now 10x greater than ENDF/B-VIII but the average resonance    8237 1451
 contribution is down by a factor of 2.                           8237 1451
                                                                  8237 1451
 The resolved resonance was extended from 1 MeV to 1.5 MeV using  8237 1451
 Carlton transmission data [ref04] and RPI scattering             8237 1451
 measurements with nautral lead [ref12]. Due to spin              8237 1451
 insensitivity of certain transmission energies, a regressive     8237 1451
 method of spin assignments was developed using SAMMY,            8237 1451
 NJOY [ref13], and MCNP [ref14]. Cross section integral           8237 1451
 comparisons were made between R-matrix and pointwise cross       8237 1451
 sections to ensure no more than 1% in integral cross section     8237 1451
 was changed as a result of formalism change.                     8237 1451
